---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const PAGINATION = {
  postsPerPage: 6
};

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  // Mock data - in a real project this would read MDX files
  const posts = [
    {
      slug: 'first-steps-bitcoin',
      title: 'First Steps in the Bitcoin World',
      description: 'Complete guide for beginners who want to start their journey in the Bitcoin ecosystem.',
      date: '2024-03-15',
      readTime: '5 min read',
      category: 'Guide',
      author: 'Bitcoin Expert',
      content: `
# First Steps in the Bitcoin World

Welcome to the fascinating world of Bitcoin. If you're new to cryptocurrencies, this guide will help you understand the basic concepts and take your first steps with confidence.

## What is Bitcoin?

Bitcoin is a decentralized cryptocurrency created in 2009 by a person or group known as Satoshi Nakamoto. Unlike traditional currencies, Bitcoin is not controlled by any government or financial institution.

### Main Features

- **Decentralization**: There is no central authority controlling Bitcoin
- **Transparency**: All transactions are public on the blockchain
- **Security**: Advanced cryptography protects your funds
- **Limited Supply**: Only 21 million bitcoins will ever exist

## How to Get Started

### 1. Education

Before investing, it's essential to understand how Bitcoin works. Take time to learn about:

- Blockchain technology
- Wallets and secure storage
- Risks and benefits
- Market analysis

### 2. Create a Wallet

You'll need a digital wallet to store your bitcoins. Options include:

- **Software wallets**: Apps for your computer or mobile
- **Hardware wallets**: Physical devices for maximum security
- **Paper wallets**: Paper storage for long-term holding

### 3. Buy Bitcoin

You can buy Bitcoin through:

- Cryptocurrency exchanges
- Bitcoin ATMs
- P2P (person-to-person) trading
- Broker services

## Tips for Beginners

### Start with Small Amounts

Don't invest more than you're willing to lose. Start with small amounts to familiarize yourself with the process.

### Maintain Security

- Use strong, unique passwords
- Enable two-factor authentication
- Consider using a hardware wallet for significant amounts
- Never share your private keys

### Be Patient

Bitcoin prices can be volatile. Don't make impulsive decisions based on short-term price movements.

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Not doing your own research** (DYOR)
2. **Following advice without verification**
3. **Storing everything on exchanges**
4. **Forgetting to backup your wallets**
5. **Panicking during price drops**

## Useful Resources

- [Bitcoin.org](https://bitcoin.org/) - Official Bitcoin site
- [Bitcoin Whitepaper](https://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf) - Satoshi's original document
- Bitcoin forums and communities
- Educational courses on cryptocurrencies

## Conclusion

Bitcoin represents a revolutionary innovation in the world of finance. While it may seem complex at first, with proper education and a prudent approach, anyone can participate in this new digital economy.

Remember to always do your own research and never invest more than you can afford to lose.

---

*Ready to start your Bitcoin journey? Keep learning and explore the opportunities offered by this incredible technology.*
      `
    }
  ];

  return posts.map(post => ({
    params: { slug: post.slug },
    props: post
  }));
}

const { title, description, date, readTime, category, author, content } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout title={title}>
	<article class="py-20">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
			<!-- Header -->
			<header class="mb-12">
				<div class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">
					<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-bitcoin-orange text-white text-xs font-semibold rounded-full">
						{category}
					</span>
					<time datetime={date}>
						{new Date(date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
							year: 'numeric', 
							month: 'long', 
							day: 'numeric' 
						})}
					</time>
					<span>•</span>
					<span>{readTime}</span>
				</div>
				
				<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
					<span class="gradient-text">{title}</span>
				</h1>
				
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">{description}</p>
				
				<!-- Author Info -->
				<div class="flex items-center space-x-4 p-4 bg-dark-card border border-dark-border rounded-lg">
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-bitcoin-orange/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
						<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-bitcoin-orange" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
							<path d="M12 12c2.21 0 4-1.79 4-4s-1.79-4-4-4-4 1.79-4 4 1.79 4 4 4zm0 2c-2.67 0-8 1.34-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.66-5.33-4-8-4z"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<div>
						<div class="font-semibold">{author}</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-gray-400">Expert Bitcoin Analyst</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</header>
			
			<!-- Content -->
			<div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
				<Fragment set:html={content} />
			</div>
			
			<!-- Tags -->
			<div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark-border">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Tags</h3>
				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
					<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dark border border-dark-border text-gray-300 text-sm rounded-full hover:border-bitcoin-orange hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors cursor-pointer">
						Bitcoin
					</span>
					<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dark border border-dark-border text-gray-300 text-sm rounded-full hover:border-bitcoin-orange hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors cursor-pointer">
						Beginners
					</span>
					<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dark border border-dark-border text-gray-300 text-sm rounded-full hover:border-bitcoin-orange hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors cursor-pointer">
						Guide
					</span>
					<span class="px-3 py-1 bg-dark border border-dark-border text-gray-300 text-sm rounded-full hover:border-bitcoin-orange hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors cursor-pointer">
						Cryptocurrencies
					</span>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Share Buttons -->
			<div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark-border">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Share</h3>
				<div class="flex space-x-4">
					<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
						Share on Twitter
					</button>
					<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-800 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-900 transition-colors">
						Share on Facebook
					</button>
					<button class="px-4 py-2 bg-gray-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
						Copy Link
					</button>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Related Posts -->
			<div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-dark-border">
				<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">
						<span class="gradient-text">Related Articles</span>
				</h3>
				
				<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
					<article class="bg-dark-card border border-dark-border rounded-lg p-6 card-hover">
						<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors">
							<a href="/blog/blockchain-explained">Blockchain Explained for Humans</a>
						</h4>
							<p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">Understand the technology behind Bitcoin in a simple and clear way.</p>
							<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">8 min read</div>
					</article>
					
					<article class="bg-dark-card border border-dark-border rounded-lg p-6 card-hover">
						<h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3 hover:text-bitcoin-orange transition-colors">
							<a href="/blog/bitcoin-wallets-security">Bitcoin Wallets: Security Guide</a>
						</h4>
							<p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">Learn to protect your bitcoins with the best security practices.</p>
							<div class="text-sm text-gray-500">10 min read</div>
					</article>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</article>
</Layout>
